This home truly showcases value! If location and presentation is a must for you, then 9a Malleehen Street is a MUST see! Enquire today!

Description:
Unforgettable Elegance and Luxury!
This beautiful two-storey family residence impressive in scale, presentation and finishes of grand proportions, leaves nothing to be desired in terms of a family lifestyle.
Beginning with an intimate formal lounge, leads to the guest bedroom and bathroom, the floorplan flows effortlessly to an open plan living/dining domain overseen by an impressive kitchen and quality fittings such as upgraded stainless steel appliances, 40 mm stone finishes, ample cabinetry plus generous work space and storage.
The impressive upper level contains a large family retreat, accompanied by exquisite style four bedrooms and two bathrooms, main bedroom includes a large balcony, lavish en suite with double vanity, oversized shower and a huge walk-in-robe.
Sliding doors open from living area to covered tiled alfresco with artificial grass - perfect for family dinners or large scale entertaining.
Features include ducted heating, evaporative cooling, double garage with remote control and internal access, stylish interiors including contemporary neutral décor, quality fixtures and fittings throughout including window furnishings, high ceiling, light fittings, fully landscaped front and rear gardens surrounds.
Situated in a quiet location of Upper Point Cook estate close to local schools, public transport and the Sneydes road interchange.

Description:
Picturesque Single Level Stunner.
Often sought but rarely found, this property presents an excellent opportunity to obtain an immaculately maintained home situated in a prime location in the highly coveted Upper Point Cook estate. This beautiful, as-new property is perfect for first home buyers, investors and downsizers alike. It offers delightful dimensions, designer style and superior fixtures and fittings throughout, in addition to being zoned to the highly recommended Point Cook College and Stella Maris Primary School. You will be impressed by the thoughtful floorplan, which encompasses an inviting sun-drenched living and dining area that flows seamlessly through glass doors to a flawlessly landscaped and extensive decking outdoor entertaining area, perfect for entertaining with family and friends. The spectacular kitchen of generous proportions includes oversized stainless-steel appliances, stone benchtops and walk-in pantry, all of which ensure culinary elegance and efficiency. A considerately designed master bedroom features a private dressing room, which comprises a walk-in wardrobe, an exquisite ensuite, complete with modern fixtures and extra-large stylish shower. Every comfort has been incorporated, including floorboards, ducted heating, air conditioning and a single remote garage with internal access. This wonderful property is located just a leisurely stroll from delightful parklands, easy access onto the freeway, and effortless access to outstanding proposed facilities that Upper Point Cook will have to offer in the near future. The close proximity to Point Cook Town Centre and child care centres further enhance the appeal of this outstanding home, which is simply fantastic from every perspective!

Build Your Dream Home
Positioned in the Gateway Estate and sitting on 608 square metres with 16-metre frontage and 38-metre length, this allotment is a rare opportunity for young families, families up-sizing, home business runners, young professionals and retirees who desire a safe and quiet place.
Located 2km from Williams Landing shopping centre and train station with ample carparks, and 4km from Laverton train station, enjoy a 30 minutes peaceful train ride to the Flinders Street or Southern Cross Station every morning. Alternatively, drive 20 minutes to CBD with easy access to the Princes Freeway.
9 minutes drive to Stockland Point Cook Shopping Centre, parklands and Sanctuary lake.
The land is close to Westbourne Grammar Schools and Truganina South Primary School. Plan weekend getaways in Werribee Free Range Zoo, Geelong, and the Great Otway National Park.
Walking distance to the playground and BBQ area. All your friendly neighbours are established, and some have been living in the neighbourhood for more than 5 years.
Be quick!
This won't last long!

Address: 29/1 Greg Norman Drive Sanctuary Lakes VIC 3030
Description:
Supreme Sanctuary Lakes Location
As we are aware during this critical time and social distancing, it is now mandatory that you register for a private inspection and follow the government guidelines in this video https://youtu.be/2WCtGFNENYU
Positioned in the hot spot of Sanctuary Lakes, living on Greg Norman Drive is living at its finest.
If you are down-sizing, looking to invest or a first home buyer then this is the perfect opportunity for you. You will get all your boxes ticked for this beautifully presented home you've been waiting for.
The large driveway entrance with manicured lawn and landscape gardens will straightaway impress you as you walk in. Warmly greeted by cosy formal lounge room upon entrance with easy flowing floor plan to the open plan kitchen, living and dining including powder room.
Your kitchen features a generous size island bench which overlooks the main living/ dining and outdoor spaces. Complimented by stainless steel appliances including near new dishwasher with ample overhead cupboards and draws for all your kitchen storages.
Friends and family can spread out from the dining to the large outdoor entertaining area, fully paved and nurtured. Enough space for your gardens as well as great backyard entertainer's choice all year around. There's also a fully paved path surrounding the entire home for your convenience.
Stroll up the staircase to a central retreat area upstairs. The second level comes with three bedrooms all including their own balcony to enjoy. The master bedroom comes with walk-in robe and ensuite with double vanity. The other two bedrooms include built-in robes sharing a main central bathroom.
Adding further value to the home are features such as refrigerated cooling and heating, high ceilings, downlights throughout the house, ceiling fans in bedrooms and living areas. Fully landscaped front yard with double remote garage, built in shelves, large external storage space underneath the staircase for your convenient and back to base monitored alarm system.
Take a beautiful stroll around the forever famous lakes or walking along the creek and wetland reserve. This perfect location allows you to walk or a short drive to the Sanctuary Lakes Shopping Centre and local schools. Sanctuary Lakes Resort Estate offers 24 hours security patrol and a recreational club including gym and swimming pool.
Perfect home to start your property portfolio!
